<Date>1616252715945<//Date><rate>5< /rate>< Text>
Long story short. I have a 13 year old Suzuki GSX1300BK (B-King) that needed a new voltage regulator / rectifier. I called these guys and they put my mind at ease because they were so professional, friendly and helpful. They got the part for me in one day! (and I got a discount on it, so it was a good deal)

I asked if I could test it (using my shop manual testing procedure and my voltmeter) in their store before leaving and they agreed and said that if there was a problem, they would take care of it right then.

I went there, got the part and tested it.....it was perfect and I am putting my ride back together today (the next day).

Glad to know that old-fashioned values of courtesy and professionalism are still alive at Corona Motorsports!<//Text>

<Name>K Dodd< /Name><Time>1550797744787< /Time><Rate>5</Rate>< review>
So far some of the best customer service I have ever experienced in my life. They gave me the best price on a new Can Am Maverick X3 over the phone with no haggling or nonsense. My Can Am overheated the following day (Turned our to be just a hose clamp which was improperly installed by the factory) Not only were they extremely apologetic, but they drove all the way to Yucaipa to pick it up and fixed the same day. <Name>Y Yuan< /Name><time>1630044268079<//time><Rating>1<//Rating>< text>
Such a bad experience at the pro shop. I booked a practice round for a Junior tournament for my 12 year old daughter and paid $25 online. The tee time was 1:30 pm on a weekday. < user_name>
andy flick< /user_name>
< date>
1617076410693</date>
< Rating>
5< /Rating>
< Review>
Temecula Creek offers a beautiful but forgiving and challenging course to golfers of all skill levels. TC has some of the best-kept greens, fairways, and tee boxes, yet offers great prices for a round. The location is right off of I-15 which is convenient. WRT the highway, you get an up-close experience with on some holes, but you‚Äôre never really staring on top the highway like you would at San Clemente or Goat Hill. Some holes have beautiful vistas which you can see for miles around and even some snow-capped mountains in the distance. Pace of play is generally ok but can get backed up on weekends as you‚Äôd expect. The good news is that their oaks and creek courses generally have wide open fairways which are well kept making for easy finds of errant tee shots (like mine!). Stonehouse requires a bit more precision as there are many blind holes and elevation changes within this 9-hole set. Overall a fantastic facility with great service. Highly recommend.< /Review>
<Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMS6sXRLfYaz-c6IJyLthfkf8SBmbdhmUsgH_dy=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMqDskwjeJyjOArN0ANweCp7ZOu8qsUZLRRrsDV=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOQg6oaW0-IzIhuUDVCcMmmVe2i6wKhCliMURQG=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><Response>None< /Response><Gmap_id>0x80db81ef3eec374d:0x97f0a46c200441fe</Gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
<rating>5< /rating><GmapID>0x80db81ef3eec374d:0x97f0a46c200441fe<//GmapID>< user_id>
101604830138930548509<//user_id>
<response>None< /response>< Text>
So... I played my first and second game of golf (ever) here, and as a beginner golfer I think it was ana amazing experience. I've been to driving ranges at various courses so I've been to many courses, but never played until my stay here it the resort with the unlimited golr package. The stuff here is so incredibly helpful.

The Marshall would wave and ask if we were having a good time. The entire staff was so welcoming.

I ended up losing my head cover for my driver during the last 9 of the holes that we played. We don't live in town at all... So I was pretty bummed that I lost it since my clubs were a special gift. Well... 10 mins after I left... The pro shop called us to get me my cover back. I didn't even give them my phone number. They just remembered us!

So hospitable. The restaurant (Cork and Fire) was equally as awesome. The food was insanely good (you've got to have the wagyu and the brussels sprouts), and the bartender took the time to make my favorite cocktail for me (which required blue cheese stuffed olives). (I believe her name was Toni).

My stay and experience was amazing. Highly recommend it!< /Text>

In A Nutshell:

-The Ginger Cafe location in Gilroy is very good.
-They had outdoor seating (before it was banned due to stay-at-home orders 12/6/20).
-The service was excellent, I hope they can keep their staff.
-The food is very plentiful, the dim sum, fried rice & pad thai were all excellent & super tasty.
-If you are shopping at the Gilroy Premium Outlets in the future & need some food, I think you should consider eating a meal here.

Overall, the food quality is high-end & felt pretty healthy w/ good ingredients, definitely good food!</text>

< Review>
This qas our first time dining inside since the pandemic began.   The food was delicious and the portions were dinner sized.  I had Chicken Pad Thai and ended up boxing up more than half to take home. They socially distance.  They have customers write down their contact info prior to being seated  to help with contact tracing in the event there is an outbreak. They provide a small piece of paper with instructions on face mask etiquette while dining inside.  The staff were polite, the service was great! We will definitely be back!< /Review>

Unfortunately here the salad dressing can not be switched on a different salad. Meaning the salad dressing that is listed on the menu is the only one you can have for that salad. For example, the Chinese chicken salad has dressing and you can not have the
dressing that comes on the chicken cucumber salad instead. I am really disappointed, they do not want to accommodate for a choice of a simple salad dressing. I was looking so forward to trying the Ginger Cafe but the customer service is lacking here. Letting the customers inquire different tastes and trying diffetent sauces. Will let the customer have a chance in finding something they really enjoy eating and want to come back for more. Because when it comes down to it a REAL GOOD CHINESE SALAD it's all about the DRESSING they put on it.The dressing on it they use is not good. The sad thing about this if they gave you a choice to use the chicken cucumber sauce it would be 100x better. Customers service is the key to success no matter what type of food you serve.</Review>

< review>
It was our first time in this place. My wife was craving for dimsums while we were shopping in the outlets. The place has a nice ambiance with high ceiling and such. We were seated right away but we waited for 15mins for someone to approach us. We've been trying to make an eye contact with anyone but  we felt that we were being avoided or maybe they're just too busy. Then a tall blonde server walked our direction. She was going to the bar as we were seated on the corner of it. We got her attention and she asked if we're ready to order. We ordered our food and then we asked their drinks options. She quickly got a drinks menu from another table and then she asked if we want to start with the food first. We agreed as we were starving and they were busy. We didnt want to wait for another long time for our food. 15 mins after we ordered  our drinks, one of our apprtizers came in. They havent even served us waters yet. We were trying to get anyones attention and a small brunette server passed by us. We asked her for waters and small plate for condiments. She said ok but she never came back. After 10 more minutes, a guy brought our fried rice entree. We asked him for waters and he gave it to us right away. After we finished our fried rice, the rest of our appetizers and drink order was brought by a different lady. Everything was a hot mess. Nobody checked on us. The blonde lady only came back for our check. The food was ok but the service made the dining experience terrible. Our check was $65. It wasnt that expensive but our money was better off to Panda Express.<//review>

Ordered the pineapple fried rice, it was really good and tasted authentic like what you get in southeast asia! Service is prompt as well.
The price is value for money given the large serving size (the fried rice dish alone can serve 4 typical Asians)

It is a short walk from the gilroy outlets and a good place to rest your feet and fuel up on food.

<Text>What an experience it was finding this hidden jewel. The estate gives you amazing view on a bright and clear Temecula day. <text>Our AC unit went out yesterday July 1st...when our area was experiencing upper 90s to lower 100 degree heat this week....

Scheduling an appointment with Performance Based Heating & Air was fast and easy. Jacob (and his son) arrived early by approximately one hour of their scheduled time window. We received a text notification they were on the way. The gentlemen were polite, educated us on AC unit maintenance, and informed us what the problem was. They notified us about an online discount which gave us $50 off the standard price to replace the capacitor for a total of $200 out the door. They completed the job within 10 minutes, from start to finish. Now we have cold AC blowing throughout our house (which got up to 90f inside).

I'm very satisfied with the experience/doing business with PBH&A and highly recommend to friends and family in the surrounding "mother-lode" areas (Tuolumne, Calaveras, Angels Camp, Sonora, etc.) for AC/Heating repair needs.

< Text>
Like most cabins built in the late 1970s, our cabin relied on a wood burning stove and electric wall heaters for heat. There was no central heating system and certainly no air conditioning. We eventually changed the wood burning stove over to a propane unit with a thermostat which helped, but the upstairs bedrooms would remain cold in the winter and unbearably hot during the summer. Having to run the electric wall heaters just to keep the cabin comfortable was getting expensive. Last summer was the last straw so to speak. We needed to do something to make the cabin more comfortable for ourselves and our guests.
Enter Jacob from Performance Based Heating and Air. We were getting quotes for systems from several contractors. Initially I was opposed to the room air systems, but after investigating the systems they seemed like the best option for our application. Jacob was able to meet our needs with the best price and the best warranty. We needed to be able to control the system remotely using the internet and that is what he provided. He explained the pros and cons of the available options and worked with us to make sure the installation would be aesthetically pleasing. The installation went off without any issues in the time allotted.
Basically Jacob did what he said he could do, he was responsive, honest, giving us a great price, a great warranty, and now a comfortable cabin.
Thank you Jacob and Performance Based Heating and Air!< /Text>

<rate>5< /rate>< review>
We've had them out twice.  Once last January (2016), and once a week ago (October 2016).  Needless to say, we know where we'll be going for all of our HVAC needs!
Last January, we had them out to check out an old unit (30+ years!) at our house.  They saw how old it was, but still took it apart to find out what was wrong and told us that they might be able to fix it if we wanted, but some of the parts might be hard to get.  Alternatively, they could replace it.  Not only did they beat the big box on the price point, but the quality and speed of their work was excellent!  Less than a week after diagnosing our unit as just about dead, they were out fabricating sheet metal, getting the new unit in and hauling off the old unit.  We were able to go to sleep that night with sweet heat flowing through our house once again!
That brings us to this October.  We wanted to get our mini-split checked as it had started leaking water, as well as getting the other systems checked out before winter really kicked in.  They took a look at the mini-split and almost immediately diagnosed the issue.  After looking at our ducts, they recommended we get them replaced soon - either now, or in a few months.  During the entire process, they told us pros and cons to getting things done or waiting.  Well, we said "go for it" and a week later they were out replacing ducts and fixing the mini-split.  Needless to say, this is the best our system has performed since we moved in 2.5 years ago!
Both experiences with them have been extremely positive.  They act professionally, and with class.  I highly recommend Jacob as you know the work will be done when he says it will be done, and you won't have to call someone else out to fix it as he gets it done right the first time.</review>

< Review>
Jacob used a combination of common sense and electronic monitoring to figure out that a 15 year old AC system was not repairable.  He tried his best and replaced parts that he suspected might be causing the issue.
His knowledge such as "This system uses R-22, which will no longer be available in 2 years" helped me decide to replace the unit with a newer, more efficient system - that uses current refrigerant.  By the time he left, he had figured out how to get the install scheduled in a timely manner, although he's pretty booked up at the moment.

Jacob's crew installed a new AC system (both outside and inside) which now works great!   The crew included his brother and two other techs that worked efficiently and effectively.  Their only issue was that Jacob is too cheap to buy them walkie-talkies!  They tested their connections with both pressure and vacuum to make sure there would not be any issues.</Review>

< user_name>
Miguel Amarillas<//user_name>
<Time>1574317724054</Time>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Text>
Aladdin's definitely has the market cornered on Mediterranean food in San Diego. It's often a favorite for a Sunday lunch with my family.

While the location is convenient to the 805 freeway, the parking can be a hassle. It shares the parking lot with other businesses, and while it looks large, it's surprisingly small. The restaurant is super casual, but it feels nice and open. It's always clean, and inviting.

You can't beat the food there. We usually get the Meza Platter - a dish that comes with 8 small dishes that includes hummus, babaganoush, chicken, lamb, and a bunch of other things, along with a pizza. The baklava is great too. Served with ice cream. These three things fed 5 hungry adults. Service is standard and prices are very reasonable.

This place could easily host large parties and kids are always welcomed there.

I always look forward to going to Aladdin's.</Text>

<Review>I eat lunch at Aladdin'sat least twice a month and often twice a week.  The quality of food is of the highest level, and the service never disappoints.  I recommend Aladdin without reservation!<//Review><rate>5<//rate>< time>

<user_name>Miguel Amarillas<//user_name>< Text>
Aladdin's definitely has the market cornered on Mediterranean food in San Diego. It's often a favorite for a Sunday lunch with my family.

While the location is convenient to the 805 freeway, the parking can be a hassle. It shares the parking lot with other businesses, and while it looks large, it's surprisingly small. The restaurant is super casual, but it feels nice and open. It's always clean, and inviting.

You can't beat the food there. We usually get the Meza Platter - a dish that comes with 8 small dishes that includes hummus, babaganoush, chicken, lamb, and a bunch of other things, along with a pizza. The baklava is great too. Served with ice cream. These three things fed 5 hungry adults. Service is standard and prices are very reasonable.

This place could easily host large parties and kids are always welcomed there.

I always look forward to going to Aladdin's.< /Text>

<Review>I don't know where to begin. My wife ordered the lentil soup. It was pureed. I've never had pureed lentils at a Mediterranean restaurant. Maybe I've been eating at inauthentic restaurants or maybe this was just not prepared in the traditional manner. I ordered a chicken shawarma sandwich. It was not only greasy, dripping with brown oil, but covered in some indescribable sauce - one I've never had in 53 years of eating Mediterranean food. There were no tomatoes, lettuce or any type of yogurt-based sauce that I've always seen served with shawarma. Again, maybe I've had inauthentic food. Finally, the dolma were the type that have been marinated in tomato sauce. I prefer them without sauce, so this is a preference issue rather than one of authenticity. Regardless, they were not my favorite. Ultimately, this was not a good experience for us, and I don't intend to return.< /Review><name>David Miller</name><resp>None</resp>< Time>

Best mediterranean food in San Diego, and incredible value.

My coworkers go here, and my friends eat here. Within seconds of walking in, we're greeted, and treated like family.

I usually order a chicken shwarma sandwich, and it's hot, fresh, and at my table in minutes.

<userid>101520184619030112062<//userid>< user_name>
Tricia Pooladi<//user_name>
< Date>
1551755325411</Date>
<rating>3</rating>< text>
Cute atmosphere, wide selection of herbal teas and Mediterranean foods. They have hookah, so I think it's a hookah bar at night. The falafel appetizer was really delicious. I wish they served it Amsterdam Falafel style (WDC friends know what I'm talking about). Comes with pita triangles and tahini. I ordered a Greek salad, and the Greek salad was very good - I made little falafel pitas with the salad.
Mylo got the Fatoush salad, and it looked a little lacking - seemed to be light on the s'mac but they were really skimpy on the pita chips and didn't have feta on it although you can add it. Salad itself was large. Dave got the lamb schwarma and he said it was good. It came with a nice little greek salad, but I will have to try the schwarma for myself -- looked like it might be dry. Turkish coffee is delicious. Has a bit of minty flavor, which was quite pleasant.

Meal menu is a bit overpriced, service can be slow.</text>

What a place we chose for Mothers day, got 2 thumbs up.

I was under immense pressure taking Wife out for Lunch on Mothers day, who is picky and can afford very small room of error. But she was blown away by the food.
We ordered, Lamb Biriyani, Pita bread with Garlic sauce, Chicken Tika Kabob and Kanafa.

Everything was so perfect along with our Waitress Dana, she was very pleasant. To end, Kanafa stole our hearts. We will go there again, soon. For Garlic Sausce and Kanafa :)

Mothers day was succesful, mission accomplished. She even forgot that i did not get her flowers ;)<//review>
